Package: DMRIntTk
Type: Package
Title: Integrate DMR sets predicted on a methylation array dataset
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Wenjin Zhang
Maintainer: The package maintainer <zhangwenjin@sklmg.edu.cn>
Description: This package is developed for integrating multiple DMR sets predicted from different DMR prediction methods on the same methylation array dataset. Before DMR integration, DMRIntTk provides DMRInt_bumphunter, DMRInt_ProbeLasso, DMRInt_combp, DMRInt_ipdmr and DMRInt_mCSEA functions to help users identify DMR sets on methylation array data. Then, DMRInt_input function calculates the methylation differences of probes and DMRs and DMRInt_matrix function constructs the reliablity weight matrix for each method under different thresholds. Next, DMRInt_method and DMRInt_weight functions calculates the covered DMRs and the weights of pre-split genomic bins. Finally, the DMRInt_densitypeak function clusters all genomic bins based on density peak clustering and returns the integrated DMR set according to the user's preference.
